node.text:
“Saturn encounter” by @astronophilos

“Two days ago, a new encounter between Saturn and the Moon took place. As usual, this is an "apparent" encounter, as seen from Earth. Jupiter was also present not far away! This composition illustrates this rapprochement. However, you know my style, and for a more artistic rendering, no scale (relative distances/sizes) has been respected. Perhaps one day I'll be able to curb my artistic skills to show you a more realistic vision of it!”

node.text:
Yesterday‘s Full Moon captured by talented @rami_astro 🌕🔥

"The reddish orange color of the Moon soon after the Moon rise is due to the ongoing wildfires that's occurring in the west, mainly in Nevada. I was surprised to see the impact of this reach the east coast and the color in the image was a sort of evidence for this phenomenon. In my own assumptions, the wildfire smoke is diffusing the sun rays coming from the west, which in return are being refracted by the atmosphere, and finally ending on the Moon to project this color while the Moon is still in a low position. As the Moon got higher, the color went back to normal as no further refracted light was projected on it."

Follow @spaceclub for more!

Happy Moon Day Giveaway! 🌙  We're giving away a limited edition Apollo 50th anniversary @movaglobes to celebrate one of the most incredible achievements in human history! It features NASA's Apollo 50th logo and the official mission patches showcasing where the Apollo spacecraft touched down on the lunar surface.

Enter to win👇

1) LIKE this post! 

2) TAG as many friends as you want in SEPERATE COMMENTS!

3) FOLLOW @movaglobes + @spaceclub

4) (BONUS) share the post in your story for an additional entry and tag @spaceclub + @movaglobes 
———————————

The winner will be mentioned on July 27, 2021.

Good luck to all!

Per Instagram rules, this giveaway is in no way sponsored, administered, or associated with Instagram, Inc. or Celestron. By entering, entrants confirm that they are 13+ years of age, release Instagram of responsibility, and agree to Instagram's terms of use.

node.text:
LANDING CONFIRMED on this historic day! 🎉🧑‍🚀
Congratulations to @jeffbezos and the complete team of @blueorigin!🚀🎊

Amazon founder Jeff Bezos blasted to the edge of space and spent a few minutes outside Earth's atmosphere Today on the first crewed flight from his company Blue Origin.

An elated Bezos could be heard calling it "the best day ever" after landing back on Earth.

The milestone launch in the modern commercial space race comes on the 52nd anniversary of Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin's moon landing in 1969, though the space-faring landscape has evolved by giant leaps since then as billionaires emerge as key players driving the new race to the cosmos.

Bezos, who holds the title of the richest man in the world per Bloomberg data, has said the spaceflight will fulfill a lifelong dream and he is also curious how it will "change" him.

Via Catherine Thorbecke (ABC News)
Follow @spaceclub for more!

node.text:
Today, 52 years ago, Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin stepped out onto the lunar surface and their fellow crew mate, Michael Collins, stayed in orbit around the moon. 🧑‍🚀🧑‍🚀🧑‍🚀🚀

Aldrin is the last crew member alive to celebrate this anniversary. 

Watch our current story, click on the countdown and turn on reminders! There‘s a fantastic giveaway on @spaceclub in a few hours! 🔔🎉

Image by friend of the house @daryavaseum, captured two days ago.

Follow @spaceclub for more! ✨
